ODE VII.

The natural meaning of the Ode is, ‘ The world is sull os sair spots, but your own Tibur is the fairest. Forget your troubles, Plancus; in camp, or here in Tibur, drown care in wine. Remember how Teucer

put a bold sace on his calamity, and found a new Salamis to make up for the old?
